HTML- Hypertext Markup Language. 
Html serves as a channel for different types of content like words, images, videos etc. 
The web consist of 3 programming languages which is: HTML,CSS and JAVASCRIPT.
Html has a straight forward structure without any programming logic,loops or functions.
It is known as a DECLARATIVE LANGUAGE.
The purpose of HTML markup is to give meaning to the content and help computers understand it.

CSS- short for cascading style sheet. It is responsible for how everything looks.

JAVASCRIPT- is a programming that allows you to create really cool and interactive stuff. It can do things that Html and Css cannot even dream of. 
Html syntax- is a language used to structure web pages.
DOM- Document Object Model
Html Bold and Italics- There are 4 html elements realted to this, two for bold and two for italics.

Html lists:
-unoredered list
-ordered list
-definition list

Unordered list are the most commonly used type. For example: a list of ingrediants for a recipe. Each item is in the list is enclosed in an <li> element, which represents a list item.


Html Superscripts, subscripts and small text.
-subscripts, superscripts and small texts can be used where you need to mark-up certain bits of content as having a different meaning than the rest.
-subscripts are characters that are set above the normal baseline of text. Mathematical formulas have many superscripts. 


The titel Attribute:
-The titel attribute defines some extra information about an element.

Html links
-html links are defined with the <a> tag 
example- <a href= "https://www.w3schools.com">  This is a link</a>

Html capabilities:
Troubleshooting and Debugging html code:
There are 3 sections
1.html on the left
2.css in the middle
3.more options on the right

Html Attributes:
The class attribute <p class="intro">


ARIA ROLES:
- Aria roles are like extra attributes that we can add to html elements to make them more meaningful and help browsers understand what they represent.

Html SVG Graphics
SVG(scalable vector graphics)

What is svg ?
-stands for scalable vector graphics.
-is used to define vector based graphics for the web.
-svg defines graphics in xml format.
-each element and attribute in svg files can be animated.
-svg is a w3c recommendation. 

The <svg> element:
-The html <svg> element is a container for svg graphics.


Html media
-multimedia on the web is sound, music, videos.movies and animations.
-the common way to discover the type of a file, is to look at the file extension.

color adding to a website formula:
<body style="background:grey">

Html canvas graphics
-The html <canvas> element is used to draw graphics on a web page.

What is html canvas?
-the html <canvas> element is used to draw graphics on the fly via Javascript.
-the <canvas> element is only a container for graphics. You must use javascript to actually draw the graphics.
Canvas examples: a canvas is a rectangular area on an html page. By default,a canvas has no border and no content.
The mark-up looks like this: <canvas id="mycanvas" width="200" height="200"></canvas>

































